    "It is straightforward to infer from the above that d is symmetric.",
    "Similarly, d(x, x) = 0 is clear.",
    "Next, d(x, y) = 0 implies d B (x, y) = 0 < T and, hence, 0 = d(x, y) = d E (x, y).",
    "Since d E is a metric, we infer x = y.",
    "Hence, what remains to be shown is that d fulfills the triangle inequality d(x, z) ≤ d(x, y) + d(y, z) for all x, y, z."
